nald L.|title=Creating the Illusion: A Fashionable History of Hollywood Costume Designers|year=2015|publisher=Running Press|isbn=978-0-762-45807-3|ref=harv|oclc=963893175}}\n*{{cite book|last=Kimball|first=Stanley|title=Heber C. Kimball: Mormon Patriarch and Pioneer|publisher=University of Illinois Press|year=1986|ref=harv|isbn= 978-0-252-01299-0|orig-year=1981|oclc=16122343}}\n*{{cite book|last=Kirkham|first=Pat|title=Women Designers in the USA, 1900-2000: Diversity and Difference|ref=harv|publisher=Yale University Press|year=2002|isbn=978-0-300-09331-5|oclc= 925656148}}\n*{{cite book|last=Klepper|first=Robert K.|title=Silent Films, 1877\u20131996: A Critical Guide to 646 Movies|publisher=McFarland|ref=harv|year=2005|isbn=978-1-476-60484-8|oclc=439709956}}\n* {{cite book|last=Kotowski|first=Mariusz|title=Pola Negri: Hollywood's First Femme Fatale|publisher=University Press of Kentucky|year=2014|isbn=978-0-813-14490-0|ref=harv|oclc= 881701106}} \n*{{cite book|last=Lambert|first=Gavin|title=Nazimova: A Biography|publisher=Alfred A. Knopf|year=1997|isbn= 978-0-679-40721-8|oclc= 717624473|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book|last=Leider|first=Emily|title=Dark Lover: The Life and Death of Rudolph Valentino|year=2003|publisher=Faber and Faber|oclc=901683955|isbn=978-0-374-28239-4|ref=harv|url=https://archive.org/details/darkloverlifedea00leid}}\n*{{cite book|last=Leider|first=Emily|title=Myrna Loy: The Only Good Girl in Hollywood|year=2012|publisher=University of California Press|isbn=978-0-52027-450-1|oclc=813210664|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book|last=Mahar|first=Karen Wood|year=2008|title=Women Filmmakers in Early Hollywood|ref=harv|publisher=Johns Hopkins University Press|isbn=978-0-801-89084-0|oclc=226358159}} \n*{{cite book|last=McGuire|first=William|year=1989|orig-year=1982|title=Bollingen: An Adventure in Collecting the Past|publisher=Princeton University Press|isbn=978-0-691-01885-0|ref=harv|oclc=23769287}}\n*{{cite book|last=McLellan|first=Diane|title=The Girls: Sappho Goes to Hollywood|year=2000|ref=harv|publisher=St. Martin's Press|isbn=978-0-312-28320-9|oclc=50707794}}\n*{{cite book|last=Morris|first=Michael|year=1991|title=Madam Valentino: The Many Lives of Natacha Rambova|publisher=Abbeville Press|isbn=978-1-558-59136-3|ref=harv|oclc=555726616|title-link=Madam Valentino: The Many Lives of Natacha Rambova}}\n*{{cite book|last=Quinn|first=D. Michael|title=Same-Sex Dynamics Among Nineteenth-Century Americans: A Mormon Example|ref=harv|year=2001|publisher=University of Illinois Press|isbn=978-0-252-06958-1|oclc=1001546076}}\n*{{cite book|last1=Rambova|first1=Natacha|last2=Pickford|first2=Hala|title=Rudolph Valentino: A Wife's Memories of an Icon|year=2009|orig-year=1926|publisher=PVG Publishing|isbn= 978-0-981-64404-2|ref=harv|oclc=618549556}}\n*{{cite book|last=Sparke|first=Penny|year=2005|title=Elsie De Wolfe: The Birth of Modern Interior Decoration|publisher=Acanthus Press|ref=harv|isbn=978-0-926-49427-5|oclc=917170478}}\n*{{cite journal|last=Vaughn|first=Heather A.|year=2006|volume=33|title=Natacha Rambova: Fashion Designer (1928\u20131931)|journal=Dress|pages=21\u201341|ref=harv|doi=10.1179/036121106805252972}} {{subscription}}\n*{{cite journal|last=Vaughn|first=Heather A.|year=2008|journal=Costume Australia|title=Violent & De nite: Natacha Rambova & her Fashion Designs|pages=26\u20139|volume=1|url=http://www.fashionhistorian.net/pdf/HeatherCostumeAustralia.pdf|ref=harv|url-status=bot: unknown|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121101145337/http://www.fashionhistorian.net/pdf/HeatherCostumeAustralia.pdf|archivedate=November 1, 2012|df=mdy-all}}\n*{{cite book|last=Williams|first=Michael|title=Film Stardom, Myth and Classicism: The Rise of Hollywood's Gods|publisher=Palgrave Macmillan|year=2013|ref=harv|isbn= 978-0-230-35544-6|oclc=982217818}}\n{{Refend}}\n\n==Further reading==\n*{{cite book|last=Cottrill|first=Jennifer|title=Women Artists and the Decorative Arts, 1880-1935: The Gender of Ornament|chapter='She would not cook the spaghetti ... ': Domestic and decorative femininity and the film designs of Natacha Rambova|pages=114\u2013137|editor1=Elliott, Bridget|editor2=Helland, Janice|publisher=Ashgate|year=2002|isbn= 978-0-754-60596-6}}\n*{{cite journal|author=Mormon Artists Group|title=A S\u00e9ance In The Mormon Tabernacle: Art And Spiritualism Of Natacha Rambova|url=https://www.mormonartistsgroup.com/new-blog/2017/10/3/a-sance-in-the-mormon-tabernacle-art-and-spiritualism-of-natacha-rambova|location=New York City, NY|date=July 2009|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20171110224625/https://www.mormonartistsgroup.com/new-blog/2017/10/3/a-sance-in-the-mormon-tabernacle-art-and-spiritualism-of-natacha-rambova|archivedate=November 10, 2017|url-status=dead|df=mdy-all}}\n*{{cite journal|last=Waterbury|first=Ruth|date=December 1922|title=Wedded and Parted, or, in other words, the story of Natacha Rambova Valentino|pages=58\u20139, 117|journal=[[Photoplay]]|url=https://archive.org/stream/photoplayvolume222chic#page/686/mode/2up/search/rambova}}\n* Zumaya, Evelyn, ''Affairs Valentino''. The Rudolph Valentino Society and Publishing LLC, 2011. {{ISBN|978-0-9827709-5-5}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|708118}}\n* [https://wfpp.cdrs.columbia.edu/pioneer/ccp-natacha-rambova/ Natacha Rambova] at the Women Film Pioneers Project, [[Columbia University]]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20121101145405/http://www.fashionhistorian.net/pdf/NatachaRambovainDressbyHAV2008-1.pdf Scan of article] on Rambova in ''Dress'' (Vol. 33), 2006, Costume Society of America\n*[https://www.loc.gov/item/mm87062130/ Natacha Rambova papers] at the [[Library of Congress]]\n* [https://umfa.utah.edu/sites/default/files/2017-05/10000_EgyptianArtLessonssm.pdf Catalog of artifacts] donated by Rambova to the [[University of Utah]] (from the Utah Museum of Fine Art's Ancient Egyptian Art collection)\n* [https://egyptology.yale.edu/collections/natacha-rambova-archive-yale-university The Natacha Rambova Archive] at [[Yale University]] (