to complete ''Pomona''<br>following Bitter's death in April 1915. Konti enlarged<br>it from a {{cvt|24|in|cm|sortable=on}} [[maquette]], added detail, and<br>made minor changes. His full-size plaster model was<br>completed in January 1916, approved by Bitter's<br>widow in February, and sent to the foundry in March.<br>The fountain was dedicated in May 1916.<ref name=\"Madigan\"/>{{rp|plate 64}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" |[[Evelyn Beatrice Longman]]\n|colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#FFDEAD\" |''Consecration'' (''L'Amour'')<ref>[https://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?session=1548H5E667D49.46&profile=ariall&source=~!siartinventories&view=subscriptionsummary&uri=full=3100001~!356363~!69&ri=3&aspect=Keyword&menu=search&ipp=20&spp=20&staffonly=&term=Longman,+Evelyn&index=.AW&uindex=&aspect=Keyword&menu=search&ri=3 Consecration], from SIRIS.</ref><ref name=\"Munson Chapter 7\"/>\n|[[File:Longman Consecration 1915.jpg|100px]]\n|modeled<br>1909\u20131912<br><br>carved<br>1914\n|colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#87CEEB\" |[[Wadsworth Athenaeum]],<br>Hartford, Connecticut\n|marble\n|{{cvt|36|in|cm|sortable=on}}\n|Exhibited in the Palace of Fine Arts at the 1915 Panama-Pacific<br>International Exposition.<br>Longman was awarded a PPIE silver medal for her sculpture.<ref name=\"PPIE Cat\"/>{{rp|239}}\n|-\n|colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#FFDEAD\" |''Fountain of Ceres''\n|[[File:Burness frontispiece p.5.jpg|100px]]\n|1915\n|colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#87CEEB\" |Forecourt, Court of the Four Seasons,<br>Panama-Pacific International Exposition\n|staff\n|\n|[[File:Court of the Four Seasons PPIE 1915.jpg|100px|right]]Forecourt, Court of the Four Seasons:\n|-\n|[[Augustus Lukeman]]\n|''Memory''<ref>[https://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?session=154ED9014O856.859&menu=search&aspect=Keyword&npp=50&ipp=20&spp=20&profile=ariall&ri=&term=Straus&index=.GW&aspect=Keyword&term=Lukeman&index=.AW&term=&index=.TW&term=&index=.SW&term=&index=.FW&term=&index=.OW&term=&index=.NW&x=13&y=12 Straus Memorial], from SIRIS.</ref><br>Titanic Memorial\n|[[File:Lukeman Memory Straus Memorial NYC SAAM-J0049736.jpg|100px]] \n|1913\u20131914\n|Straus Memorial,<br>[[Straus Park]],<br>West 106th Street (west of Broadway),<br>[[Manhattan]], New York City\n|bronze\n|{{cvt|36|in|cm|sortable=on}}\n|[[File:Straus memorial.png|100px|right]]Memorial to [[Ida Straus|Ida]] and [[Isidor Straus]], who died<br>in the 1912 sinking of the [[RMS Titanic|RMS ''Titanic'']].<br><br>The park and memorial were dedicated on<br>April 15, 1915, the third anniversary of the sinking.\n|-\n|[[Frederick MacMonnies]]\n|colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#FFDEAD\" |''Beauty''<ref>[https://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?session=A5D889162934J.929&profile=ariall&source=~!siartinventories&view=subscriptionsummary&uri=full=3100001~!17852~!4&ri=1&aspect=Keyword&menu=search&ipp=20&spp=20&staffonly=&term=MacMonnies&index=.AW&uindex=&oper=&term=Beauty&index=.TW&uindex=&aspect=Keyword&menu=search&ri=1 Beauty], from SIRIS.</ref>\n|[[File:MacMonnies Beauty NYPL SAAM-S0001588.jpg|100px]]\n|{{circa}}1911\u20131917\n|[[New York Public Library Main Branch]],<br>Fifth Avenue at East 41st Street,<br>Manhattan, New York City\n|Carrara marble\n|{{cvt|120|in|cm|sortable=on}}\n|[[File:NYPL Beauty jeh.JPG|50px|right]]Located just south of the Fifth Avenue entrance.<br><br>Munson wrote that MacMonnies used her for the<br>legs, and another model for the torso and face.{{efn|\"When Mr. MacMonnies made this charming work he showed the face and torso of a model who fitted closer in these respects to his inspiration than did mine, but my legs were better for his purposes than hers.\"<ref>Audrey Munson, \"By the 'Queen of the Artists' Studios,' Chapter 9,\" ''Hearst's Sunday Magazine'', ''San Francisco Examiner'', March 6, 1921, pp. 87\u201388.</ref>}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\" |[[Allen George Newman]]\n|''Mermaid'' (unlocated)\n|[[File:Munson NY Sun 8 June 1913.jpg|100px]]\n|1910\n|''Music of th