unda's dome.<ref name=\"Mullgardt\">{{cite book |last1=Mullgardt |first1=Louis Christian |title=The Architecture and Landscape Gardening of the Exposition \u2013 A Pictorial Survey of the Most Beautiful of the Compositions of the Panama-Pacific International Exposition |date=January 1, 1915 |publisher=Paul Elder and Company |location=San Francisco |page=160 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=6oKXXGEh8UYC&pg=160#v=onepage&q&f=false |accessdate=February 3, 2019}}</ref><br><br>The figures were recast in cast stone by Spero<br>Anargyros in 1969.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Bragman |first1=Bob |title=Save the Palace of Fine Arts? In the 60s, SF wasn't so sure. |url=https://www.sfchronicle.com/bayarea/article/Dramatic-Palace-of-Fine-Arts-reconstruction-11009452.php#photo-12561313 |accessdate=February 4, 2019 |publisher=San Francisco Chroncile |date=March 21, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n|''Consolation''<ref name=\"Mullgardt\"/>{{rp|160}}<br>(''Weeping Maidens'' or ''Drooping Maidens'')\n|[[File:Weeping-Maidens-Planter-Close-Up-.jpg|100px]]\n|colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#87CEEB\" |Pergola of the Palace of Fine Arts,<br>Panama-Pacific International Exposition\n|\n|\"In the goddesses atop the towers and minarets and in the Grecian<br>boxes adorning the Roman columns of the Palace of the Fine Arts<br>will be found the enchanting line of the [Munson's] girlish form.\"<ref name=\"Times-Dispatch\"/>\n|-\n|colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#FA8072\" |Garland figures<ref name=\"Mullgardt\"/>{{rp|162}}\n|[[File:Reliefs - Palace of Fine Arts - San Francisco, CA - DSC02454.jpg|100px]]\n|colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#87CEEB\" |Peristyle Walk, Palace of Fine Arts,<br>Panama-Pacific International Exposition\n|\n|A set of five larger-than-life, high-relief figures, repeated around<br>the four semi-circular, ground-level planters\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" |[[John Flanagan (sculptor)|John Flanagan]]\n|Medallion: ''Head of Audrey Munson''<ref name=\"Teall\">Gardner Teall, \"Art: The Mirror of America