 for the Palace of Fine Arts does not list a sculpture by French titled ''Eve''.<ref name=\"PPIE Cat\"/>{{rp|235}} ''Adam'' and ''Eve'' may be the nude couple flanking the ''Angel'' on French's ''Genius of Creation''. See [[Talk:Audrey Munson#Eve|Talk page]] for discussion.}}\n|[[File:Genius of Creation.jpeg|100px]]<br>[[File:Art in California - a survey of American art with special reference to Californian painting, sculpture and architecture past and present, particularly as those arts were represented at the (14761820756).jpg|100px]]\n|1915\n|colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#87CEEB\" |West entrance to Palace of Machinery,<br>Pamama-Pacific International Exposition\n|staff\n|\n|French was awarded a PPIE Medal of Honor for his sculpture.<ref name=\"PPIE Cat\"/>{{rp|235}}<br><br>[[File:Todd Story of Exposition vol.2 opp. p.246.jpg|100px|right]][[File:Chesterwood (Stockbridge, MA) - studio interior.JPG|100px|right]]West entrance to Palace of Machinery:<br><br>A plaster model is at [[Chesterwood (Massachusetts)|Chesterwood]],<ref>[https://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?session=1W50074G57Q75.158&profile=ariall&source=~!siartinventories&view=subscriptionsummary&uri=full=3100001~!21209~!0&ri=1&aspect=Keyword&menu=search&ipp=20&spp=20&staffonly=&term=creation&index=.GW&uindex=&oper=&term=French,+Daniel&index=.AW&uindex=&aspect=Keyword&menu=search&ri=1 Model for Creation], from SIRIS.</ref> French's<br>home and studio in Stockbridge, Massachusetts:\n|-\n|''Brooklyn''<ref>[https://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?session=154885M8018DD.11&profile=ariall&source=~!siartinventories&view=subscriptionsummary&uri=full=3100001~!21221~!7&ri=1&aspect=Keyword&menu=search&ipp=20&spp=20&staffonly=&term=Brooklyn&index=.GW&uindex=&oper=&term=French,+Daniel+Chester&index=.AW&uindex=&aspect=Keyword&menu=search&ri=1 Brooklyn], from SIRIS.</ref>\n|[[File:Allegorical Figure of Brooklyn, from the Manhattan Bridge, NYC - Daniel Chester French - Brooklyn Museum - DSC08223.JPG|100px]]\n|1916\n|rowspan=\"2\" |[[Brooklyn Museum]],<br>Brooklyn, New York City\n|granite\n|\n|rowspan=\"2\" |The pair were created to adorn the Brooklyn side of the<br>[[Manhattan Bridge]].<br><br>Relocated to exterior of the Brooklyn Museum, 1963.<br><br>At least some of the modeling for the ''Brooklyn'' figure was done by<br>Rosalie Miller.<ref> Richman, Michael, \"Daniel Chester French: An American Sculptor\u201d, The Preservation Press, Washington D.C.,  1976 p. 146</ref>\n|-\n|''Manhattan''<ref>[https://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?session=154885M8018DD.11&profile=ariall&source=~!siartinventories&view=subscriptionsummary&uri=full=3100001~!21222~!8&ri=3&aspect=Keyword&menu=search&ipp=20&spp=20&staffonly=&term=Brooklyn&index=.GW&uindex=&oper=&term=French,+Daniel+Chester&index=.AW&uindex=&aspect=Keyword&menu=search&ri=3 Manhattan], from SIRIS.</ref>\n|[[File:Allegorical Figure of Manhattan, from the Manhattan Bridge, NYC - Daniel Chester French - Brooklyn Museum - DSC08218.JPG|100px]]\n|1916\n|granite\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=\"8\" |[[Sherry Edmundson Fry]]\n|colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#FFDEAD\" |70th Street pediment<ref name=\"El Paso\"/>\n|[[File:Henry C Frick House 010.JPG|100px]]\n|1913\n|[[Frick Collection|Frick Mansion]],<br>Fifth Avenue & East 70th Street,<br>Manhattan, New York City\n|Bedford blue<br>limestone\n|\n|\n|-\n|colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#FFDEAD\" |''Maidenhood''<ref>[https://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?session=1548H5E667D49.46&profile=ariall&source=~!siartinventories&view=subscriptionsummary&uri=full=3100001~!25183~!1&ri=3&aspect=Keyword&menu=search&ipp=20&spp=20&staffonly=&term=Fry&index=.AW&uindex=&oper=&term=Maidenhood&index=.TW&uindex=&aspect=Keyword&menu=search&ri=3 Maidenhood], from SIRIS.</ref>\n|\n|1914\n|[[Brookgreen Gardens]],<br>Murrells Inlet, South Carolina\n|bronze \n|{{cvt|67.3|in|cm|sortable=on}}\n|Ex collection: Metropolitan Museum of Art<ref name=\"Munson Chapter 7\"/>\n|-\n|colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#FFDEAD\" |''Peace'' (''Maidenhood'')\n|[[File:Statue Burness PPIE p.59.jpg|80px]]\n|1914\u20131915\n|colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#87CEEB\" |Peristyle Walk,<br>Exterior of Palace of Fine Arts,<br>Panama-Pacific International Exposition\n|bronze\n|\n|Fry was awarded a PPIE silver medal for his sculpture.<ref name=\"PPIE Cat\"/>{{rp|235}}\n|-\n|Cartouche\n| \n|rowspan=\"4\" |1915\n|colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#87CEEB\" |Female nude beside shield, over great<br>arched window of Festival Hall,<ref name=\"Barry\"/>{{rp|125}}<br>Panama-Pacific International Exposition\n|rowspan=\"4\" |staff\n|\n|rowspan=\"4\" |[[File:Festival Hall Reid p.22.jpg|100px|right]]Festival Hall:\n|-\n|''Flora''<ref>\"Miss Audrey Monson and the Statue for Which She Posed,\" ''The Logan Republican'' (Utah), April 13, 1915, p. 1.[https://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn85058246/1915-04-13/ed-1/seq-1/#date1=1789&sort=relevance&rows=20&words=Audrey+Munson&searchType=basic&sequence=0&index=14&state=&date2=1963&proxtext=Audrey+Munson&y=9&x=12&dateFilterType=yearRange&page=10]</ref>\n|[[File:Statue in front of Festival Hall.jpg|100px]]\n|colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#87CEEB\" |Twin figures atop pedestals at base of<br>pylons of Festival Hall,<ref name=\"Barry\"/>{{rp|125}}<br>Panama-Pacific International Exposition\n|\n|-\n|''Torch Bearer''\n|[[File:Corner Dome figure Festival Hall.jpg|80px]]\n|colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#87CEEB\" |Figure repeated atop the four corner<br>domes of Festival Hall,<ref name=\"Barry\"/>{{rp|125}}<br>Panama-Pacific International Exposition\n|\n|-\n|''Reclining Woman'' (''Listening Woman'')<br>Pylon figure \n|[[File:Unidentified Burness p.51.jpg|100px]]\n|colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#87CEEB\" |atop east pylon of Festival Hall,<ref name=\"Barry\"/>{{rp|125}}<br>Panama-Pacific International Exposition\n|\n|-\n|''Ceres, Goddess of Agriculture''<ref>[https://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?session=1548H5E667D49.46&profil