l figures on the arcades in the<br>Court of the Four Seasons.<ref>Edward Payson Critcher, \"Sculpture and Sculptors: Panam-Pacific International Exposition,\" ''The Fine Arts Journal'', vol. 32 (February 1915), p. 47.[https://archive.org/details/jstor-25603468/page/n3]</ref><br><br>''Abundance'' was repeated sixteen times on the arcades.\n|-\n|rowspan=\"6\" |[[Isidore Konti]]\n|colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#FFDEAD\" |''The Three Graces''\n|[[File:Three Graces, Hotel Astor ballroom.jpg|100px]]\n|{{circa}}1909\n|\n|marble\n|\n|[[File:HotelAstorBallroom.jpg|100px|right]]Created for the new ballroom of the Hotel Astor,<br>opened September 29, 1909 (second balcony):<br><br>At the other end of the ballroom, a companion<br>marble group called ''The Song'' featured similar<br>figures, possibly also modeled by Munson.<ref name=\"Madigan\">{{cite book |last1=Madigan |first1=Mary Jean Smith |title=The Sculpture of Isidore Konti, 1862\u20131938: Exhibition , January 26 \u2013 March 30 1974 |date=January 1, 1974 |publisher=Hudson River Museum |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=3fwWlg-DLHMC&pg=PA26#v=onepage&q&f=false |accessdate=February 1, 2019}}</ref>{{rp|plate 26}}\n|-\n|''Three Muses''<ref>[https://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?session=1548H5E667D49.46&profile=ariall&source=~!siartinventories&view=subscriptionsummary&uri=full=3100001~!9381~!8&ri=1&aspect=Keyword&menu=search&ipp=20&spp=20&staffonly=&term=Konti&index=.AW&uindex=&aspect=Keyword&menu=search&ri=1 Three Muses], from SIRIS.</ref>\n|[[File:Three Muses (Isadore Konti).jpg|100px]]\n|undated\n|[[Hudson River Museum]],<br>Yonkers, New York\n|plaster\n|{{cvt|23|in|cm|sortable=on}}\n|\n|-\n|colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#FFDEAD\" |''Mother and Child: The Bath''<br>(Fountain Group)<ref name=\"Munson Chapter 7\"/>\n|[[File:Isidore Konti - Groupe pour fontaine.jpg|100px]]\n|{{circa}}1910\n|private collection\n|marble\n|two-thirds<br>life size<ref name=\"Madigan\"/>{{rp|plate 35}}\n|\n|-\n|colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#FFDEAD\" |''Solace''<ref name=\"El Paso\"/><ref>[https://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?session=15G077927X69M.1010&profile=ariall&source=~!siartinventories&view=subscriptionsummary&uri=full=3100001~!9385~!12&ri=1&aspect=Keyword&menu=search&ipp=20&spp=20&staffonly=&term=Konti,+Isidore&index=.AW&uindex=&aspect=Keyword&menu=search&ri=1 Solace], from SIRIS.</ref>\n|\n|1911\n|colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#87CEEB\" |Hudson River Museum,<ref name=\"Madigan\"/>{{rp|plate 46}}<br>Yonkers, New York\n|plaster\n|{{cvt|28|in|cm|sortable=on}}\n|\n|-\n|''Fame'' and ''Victory'' (relief figures)<ref name=\"Madigan\"/>{{rp|plate 51}}\n|[[File:Konti frieze Calder Sculpture of PPIE p.67.jpg|100px]]\n|{{circa}}1915\n|colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#87CEEB\" |Column of Human Progress,<br>Forecourt of the Stars,<br>Panama-Pacific International Exposition\n|staff\n|\n|[[File:The story of the exposition; being the official history of the international celebration held at San Francisco in 1915 to commemorate the discovery of the Pacific Ocean and the construction of the (14584177520).jpg|100px|right]]Four relief panels with heroic-sized figures<br>surrounded the base of the {{cvt|180|ft|m|sortable=on}}-tall<br>Column of Human Progress.<ref name=\"Madigan\"/>{{rp|plate 51}}<br><br>Munson was the model for ''Fame'' and ''Victory'',<br>which flanked the entrance to its vault.<ref name=\"Madigan\"/>{{rp|plate 51}}\n|-\n|colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#FFDEAD\" |''Pomona''\n|[[File:Pomona.jpg|100px]]\n|1915\u20131916\n|[[Pulitzer Fountain]],<br>[[Plaza Hotel#Grand Army Plaza|Grand Army Plaza]],<br>Manhattan, New York City\n|bronze\n|{{cvt|84|in|cm|sortable=on}}\n|[[File:Grand Army Plaza, NYC (2014) - 2.JPG|100px|right]]Karl Bitter's widow asked Konti to complete ''Pomona''<br>following Bitter's death in April 1915. Konti enlarged<br>it from a {{cvt|24|in|cm|sortable=on}} [[maquette]], added detail, and<br>made minor changes. His full-size plaster model was<br>completed in January 1916, approved by Bitter's<br>widow in February, and sent to the foundry in March.<br>The fountain was dedicated in May 1916.<ref name=\"Madigan\"/>{{rp|plate 64}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" |[[Evelyn Beatrice Longman]]\n|colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#FFDEAD\" |''Consecration'' (''L'Amour'')<ref>[https://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?session=1548H5E667D49.46&profile=ariall&source=~!siartinventories&view=subscriptionsummary&uri=full=3100001~!356363~!69&ri=3&aspect=Keyword&menu=search&ipp=20&spp=20&staffonly=&term=Longman,+Evelyn&index=.AW&uindex=&aspect=Keyword&menu=search&ri=3 Consecration], from SIRIS.</ref><ref name=\"Munson Chapter 7\"/>\n|[[File:Longman Consecration 1915.jpg|100px]]\n|modeled<br>1909\u20131912<br><br>carved<br>1914\n|colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#87CEEB\" |[[Wadsworth Athenaeum]],<br>Hartford, Connecticut\n|marble\n|{{cvt|36|in|cm|sortable=on}}\n|Exhibited in the Palace of Fine Arts at the 1915 Panama-Pacific<br>International Exposition.<br>Longman was awarded a PPIE silver medal for her sculpture.<ref name=\"PPIE Cat\"/>{{rp|239}}\n|-\n|colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#FFDEAD\" |''Fountain of Ceres''\n|[[File:Burness frontispiece p.5.jpg|100px]]\n|1915\n|colspan=\"1\" style=\"background:#87CEEB\" |Forecourt, Court of the Four Seasons,<br>Panama-Pacific International Exposition\n|staff\n|\n|[[File:Court of the Four Seasons PPIE 1915.jpg|100px|right]]Forecourt, Court of the Four Seasons:\n|-\n|[[Augustus Lukeman]]\n|''Memory''<ref>[https://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?session=154ED9014O856.859&menu=search&aspect=Keyword&npp=50&ipp=20&spp=20&profile=ariall&ri=&term=Straus&index=.GW&aspect=Keyword&term=Lukeman&index=.AW&term=&index=.TW&term=&index=.SW&term=&index=.FW&term=&index=.OW&term=&index=.NW&x=13&y=12 Straus Memorial], from SIRIS.</ref><br>Titanic Memorial\n|[[File:Lukeman Memory Straus Memorial NYC SAAM-J0049736.jpg|100px]] \n|1913\u20131914\n|Straus Memorial,<br>[[Straus Park]],<br